This is a study of the genetics of malaria transmission by the mosquito vector in Africa, Anopheles gambiae.

 The study focuses on the mosquito vector, not the human subjects infected with malaria.

 DNA extracted from infected mosquitoes will be analyzed genetically by microsatellite and single-nucleotide polymorphisms (SNPs) to identify mosquito genes that control mosquito resistance to malaria parasites.

